        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This is the sort of API I'm imagining:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<CR>', function()\n  if not require('vim._core.ui2').try_open_pager() then\n    -- Implement normal keybind logic here\n  end\nend)\n```\n\nOr:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<CR>', function()\n  if require('vim._core.ui2').is_recent_msg() then\n    vim.api.nvim_command('norm! g<')\n  else\n    -- Implement normal keybind logic here\n  end\nend)\n```",
