        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> If a keymap is made, this functionality breaks.\n\nWith what kind of `<CR>` mapping does it break and in what way? The \"`<CR>` to enter pager mapping\" is done in a vim.on_key() handler which receives the unmapped key. So what currently happens is that he pager is enterend _and_ the mapping is executed. Should probably consume the key:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua\nindex 9ddbca5e76..03e5f843db 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua\n@@ -526,6 +526,7 @@ local cmd_on_key = function(_, typed)\n     api.nvim_command('norm! g<')\n   end\n   set_virttext('msg')\n+  return entered and ''\n end\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-03-22T22:06:17Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38416#issuecomment-4107078022",
