        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> With what kind of `<CR>` mapping does it break and in what way?\n\nOh weird. It appears this is actually a bug report, not a feature request. I can confirm that most mappings still do keep the functionality (although as you say, the key should be consumed; weird stuff can sometimes happen otherwise).\n\n`<Nop>` seems to break this, however. `:lua vim.keymap.set('n', '<CR>', '<Nop>')` will make `<CR>` fully non-functional.\n\nPersonally, I bind `<CR>` to `'&buftype == \"\" ? \"\" : \"<CR>\"'` (with `{ expr = true }`), which broke it as well.",
